#: ../../source/modules/assistance/actors.rst:2
msgid "Defining actors and roles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/assistance/actors.rst:4
msgid "An assistance service usually defines the following roles:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/assistance/actors.rst:6
msgid ""
"**Requester** : user or group of users known to GLPI and affected by the "
"ticket;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/assistance/actors.rst:7
msgid ""
"**Technician**: ticket processing is done by a technician, by a group or by "
"a supplier;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/assistance/actors.rst:8
msgid ""
"**Watcher** : user who can follow a ticket but without modifying it; follow-"
"up can be done from GLPI interface or by receiving notifications."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/assistance/actors.rst:10
msgid ""
"Visible information and possible actions are defined by GLPI based on the "
"user's role, which is defined in user's profile:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/assistance/actors.rst:12
msgid ""
"Technicians are the actors having the most complete information on a ticket "
"and the widest possible actions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/assistance/actors.rst:13
msgid ""
"Requester and watcher will only view the information needed to fulfill "
"request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/assistance/actors.rst:15
msgid ""
"For multiple users or groups, only the first user or group is defined when "
"creating the ticket, more actors are added later. A user who cannot modify "
"actors but able to see the ticket can become a watcher."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/assistance/actors.rst:17
msgid ""
"When associating a new actor to a ticket, the number of tickets assigned to "
"this actor is visible; this eases for instance task partitioning between "
"technicians."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/assistance/actors.rst:21
msgid ""
"for users who are not known to GLPI, mail address can be associated to a "
"ticket. Default choice for requester and watcher (no selected user) allows "
"to add a mail address in these fields; for this to be available, "
"notifications must be activated (see :ref:`notification management "
"<configure_notifications>`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/modules/assistance/actors.rst:23
msgid ""
"Role attribution is done in user's authorization management (see "
":doc:`Attribute authorizations to a user "
"</modules/administration/rules/userauthorizations>`)"
msgstr ""
